│ instruction with a floating-point comparison   │
│ (`fcmp`) into the `llvm.fabs` intrinsic.       │
│ However, the transformation assumes that the   │
│ `nnan` (no NaNs) fast-math flag is set, which  │
│ is not always the case. This leads to          │
│ incorrect behavior when the input contains     │
│ signaling NaNs (SNaNs).                        │
│                                                │
│ To fix this issue, we need to ensure that the  │
│ transformation only occurs when the `nnan`     │
│ flag is set. Specifically, we should add a     │
│ check for the `nnan` flag at the beginning of  │
│ the function and return `nullptr` if the flag  │
│ is not set. This will prevent the              │
│ transformation from being applied in cases     │
│ where SNaNs are present.                       │
│                                                │
